cse:attribute.name: og:title
cse:attribute.value: Philippines sifting through horror in Typhoon Haiyan

cse:attribute.name: og:description
cse:attribute.value: As many as 10,000 people may have died when one of the most powerful typhoons ever recorded destroyed entire villages and devastated cities with huge waves and winds of nearly 150 mph.
